    <div class="callout info">
      <div class="callout-title">🎨 Generative AI Evolution (2014-2025)</div>
      <p><strong>Generative AI revolutionized content creation from adversarial training to diffusion-based approaches dominating by 2024.</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>GAN Era (2014-2021):</strong> June 2014 Goodfellow et al. introduced Generative Adversarial Networks at NeurIPS with generator-discriminator adversarial training → 2015 DCGAN (Radford et al.) stabilized training with convolutional architecture → 2016 WGAN (Arjovsky et al.) solved mode collapse using Wasserstein distance → 2017 Progressive GAN (Karras et al.) gradually increased resolution 4×4→1024×1024 → 2019 StyleGAN introduced style latent space with AdaIN → 2020 StyleGAN-2 solved blob artifacts → 2021 StyleGAN-3 eliminated texture sticking via Nyquist-Shannon theorem. Training challenges: unstable convergence, mode collapse, vanishing gradients.</li>
        <li><strong>Diffusion Breakthrough (2015-2024):</strong> 2015 Sohl-Dickstein et al. introduced diffusion using non-equilibrium thermodynamics → June 2020 DDPM (Ho et al.) foundational work requiring ~1000 steps → October 2020 DDIM (Song et al.) enabled 10-50× faster sampling → 2021 classifier guidance (Dhariwal & Nichol) used CLIP for text conditioning → April 2022 Latent Diffusion (Rombach et al.) operated in VAE compressed space → July 2022 Classifier-Free Guidance (Ho & Salimans) eliminated separate classifier → 2023 Diffusion Transformers (DiT) replaced U-Net backbones.</li>
        <li><strong>Text-to-Image Revolution (2021-2024):</strong> 2021 DALL-E original (12B autoregressive Transformer) → April 2022 DALL-E 2 (3.5B cascaded diffusion with unCLIP) → May 2022 Midjourney V1 → August 2022 Stable Diffusion (860M open-source democratizing access) → 2022 Imagen (Google T5-XXL + cascaded diffusion) → October 2023 DALL-E 3 → December 2023 Midjourney V6 → March 2024 Stable Diffusion 3 (DiT + rectified flow).</li>
        <li><strong>Video Generation (2022-2024):</strong> September 2022 Make-A-Video (Meta) → March 2023 Runway Gen-2 → February 2024 Sora (OpenAI DiT) → October 2024 Movie Gen (Meta DiT series) → 2024 Veo (Google).</li>
        <li><strong>Control & Fine-tuning (2023-2024):</strong> 2023 ControlNet added spatial conditioning for precise control → LoRA enabled fast fine-tuning with minimal parameters → 2023 Consistency Models (Song et al.) enabled 1-step generation → Rectified Flow (Liu et al. September 2022) learned straight-line trajectories.</li>
      </ul>
      <p><em>Sources: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Generative_adversarial_network" target="_blank">Wikipedia - Generative Adversarial Network</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diffusion_model" target="_blank">Wikipedia - Diffusion Model</a></em></p>
